  "translations": {
    "en": "My Master, You have perfected my form and made my appearance beautiful. So I wish I knew what You intend for me — will You burn me in the Fire, or will You settle me in Your proximity? O Allah, You have bestowed much goodness upon me and blessed me. So I wish I knew what my end will be — will You escort me to Paradise, or drive me to the Fire? O Allah, my sin is greater than the heavens and the earth, and Your vast Seat and Your great Throne. So I wish I knew — will You forgive my sin, or will You scandalize me with it on the Day of Resurrection? He did not stop saying things like this while weeping and pouring dust on his head. The wild animals surrounded him and the birds lined up above him, weeping at his weeping. So the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him and his family) drew near, freed his hands from his neck, cleaned the dust from his head, and said: O Bahlul, rejoice, for you have been freed by Allah from the Fire.",
